'''布萊恩·厄拉克'''（{{lang-en|Brian Urlacher}}，{{bd|1978年|5月25日}}），[[美式足球|美式足球]][[线卫|线卫]]，效力于[[国家橄榄球联盟|国家橄榄球联盟]]的[[芝加哥熊|芝加哥熊]]队。他大学时在[[新墨西哥大学灰狼|新墨西哥大学灰狼]]队打球。2000年选秀中被熊队于第一轮第9顺位选中，此后便一直在此效力。

厄拉克被认为是联盟中最有效率的防守球员。2000年获得[[NFL年度新秀奖|NFL年度新秀奖]]（NFL Rookie of the Year Award）后，他八次入选[[明星碗|明星碗]]<ref>Mayer, Larry, [http://www.chicagobears.com/news/NewsStory.asp?story_id=2749 Bears well-represented in Pro Bowl voting] {{Wayback|url=http://www.chicagobears.com/news/NewsStory.asp?story_id=2749 |date=20120208154052 }} (December 1, 2006), chicagobears.com, Retrieved on July 18, 2007.</ref>，并曾于2005年获评为[[NFL年度防守球员|NFL年度防守球员]]。<ref name="BearsBio">The Official Website of the Chicago Bears, [http://www.chicagobears.com/team/player79.html Roster - 54 Brian Urlacher] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081013155703/http://www.chicagobears.com/team/player79.html |date=2008-10-13 }}, chicagobears.com, Retrieved on July 18, 2007.</ref>他是球队中最受欢迎的球员之一，还曾为多家公司代言。<ref name="Jay1">Mariotti, Jay, [http://www.suntimes.com/sports/mariotti/116332,CST-SPT-jay30.article 'Overrated' Urlacher could be NFL MVP] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061201154155/http://www.suntimes.com/sports/mariotti/116332,CST-SPT-jay30.article |date=2006-12-01 }} (October 30, 2006), Chicago Sun-Times, Retrieved on July 18, 2007.</ref>[[世嘉|世嘉]]出品的游戏''NFL 2K3''中以他作为封面人物，[[耐吉|耐吉]]、[[麦当劳|麦当劳]]、Old Spice、Vitamin Water等也都曾请他代言电视广告等宣传品。<ref>Williams, Preston, [http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/09/26/AR2006092601857.htmlLook! My Uniform's on TV!]{{Dead link}} (September 28, 2006), The Washington Post, Retrieved on July 18, 2007.</ref><ref>Mattise, Nathan, [http://www.abqtrib.com/news/2007/jun/27/fans-put-their-knowledge-all-things-urlacher-test/?lobozone-story-detail=1/ Fans put their knowledge of all things Urlacher to the test] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707091718/http://www.abqtrib.com/news/2007/jun/27/fans-put-their-knowledge-all-things-urlacher-test/?lobozone-story-detail=1%2F |date=2011-07-07 }} (June 27, 2007), The Albuquerque Tribune, Retrieved on July 18, 2007.</ref>

